# Lumen Test Conventions

## FP8 / GPU tests MUST run on CUDA

FP8 ops (`torch.float8_e4m3fn`, `torch.float8_e4m3fnuz`) require CUDA. Tests using FP8 activation store, FP8 quantization, or any Lumen FP8 path must create tensors on CUDA and move modules to CUDA:

```python
# BAD — FP8 autograd breaks on CPU
mlp = LumenGatedMLP(64, 128, fp8_activation_store=True)
x = torch.randn(2, 16, 64, requires_grad=True)

# GOOD
mlp = LumenGatedMLP(64, 128, fp8_activation_store=True).cuda()
x = torch.randn(2, 16, 64, device="cuda", requires_grad=True)
```

## Leaf tensor rule for gradient SNR tests

When comparing gradients between a Lumen op and a reference (`F.linear`, `attention_ref`), the reference weight tensor MUST be a leaf. Multiplying after `requires_grad=True` creates a non-leaf tensor whose `.grad` is always `None`:

```python
# BAD — w is non-leaf (has grad_fn=MulBackward), w.grad stays None
w = torch.randn(128, 64, requires_grad=True) * 0.02

# GOOD — multiply first, then enable grad tracking
w = (torch.randn(128, 64) * 0.02).requires_grad_(True)
```

## Forward signature: always pass ALL positional args

Megatron-compatible modules (`LumenDotProductAttention`, `LumenDotProductAttentionMLA`) require `attention_mask` as a positional argument. Always pass it, even in benchmarks:

```python
# BAD
attn(q, k, v)

# GOOD
attn(q, k, v, attention_mask=None)
```

## FP8 backend auto-mapping

`LumenAttention` defaults to `backend_type="aiter_csrc"`. When `quant_type` is set (FP8 mode), the module auto-maps `aiter_csrc → aiter_triton` because `attention_fp8_quant` only accepts `aiter_triton`, `aiter_triton_fp8`, `aiter_csrc_fp8`, `aiter_asm_fp8`. Tests that want FP8 attention need not set `backend_type` explicitly; the mapping is automatic.

## Tensor dimensions must match parallel partitioning

`LumenRowParallelLinear(in_features, out_features, tp_size=N)` with `input_is_parallel=True` expects input of size `in_features / tp_size`:

```python
# BAD — input_size_per_partition = 64 / 2 = 32, but input has 64
m = LumenRowParallelLinear(64, 128, tp_size=2)
x = torch.randn(4, 64)

# GOOD
x = torch.randn(4, 32)
```

## MXFP8 quant_block_size must divide head_dim

Triton MXFP8 kernel requires `padded_head_dim % quant_block_size == 0`. When parametrizing `quant_block_size`, use a head_dim divisible by all values:

```python
# BAD — head_dim=64 not divisible by 128 or 256
@pytest.mark.parametrize("quant_block_size", [64, 128, 256])
def test_block_sizes(self, quant_block_size):
    q = torch.randn(1, 128, 4, 64, ...)  # head_dim=64

# GOOD — head_dim=256 divisible by all block sizes
    q = torch.randn(1, 128, 4, 256, ...)  # head_dim=256
```

## Read-only properties on mock objects

`SdmaTpComm.npes` and `SdmaTpComm.my_pe` are read-only `@property` attributes. Set values via the underlying `_ctx` mock, not by assignment:

```python
# BAD — raises AttributeError
comm.npes = 2
comm.my_pe = 0

# GOOD — values come from the mock context
mock_ctx.get.return_value = SimpleNamespace(my_pe=0, npes=2)
```

## Assert gradients before computing SNR

Always verify gradients are non-None before passing to `compute_snr`:

```python
assert dinput is not None, "backward did not populate input grad"
assert dweight is not None, "backward did not populate weight grad"
dinput_snr = compute_snr(ref_grad, dinput)
```
